KNOWN BUGS
==

* missing fill spans where the raster is missing for the line (eg. at the bottom of short characters
  preceded by a taller one)
* some fonts are still completely garbled
* outline type fonts are not supported yet

FEATURES
==

* packaging for Open/Net/FreeBSD
* packaging for Solaris
* packaging for Debian
* option to pad canvas width to nearest multiple of 80
* option to pad canvas height
* option to justify (left, centre, right) text on canvas
* add option to render to PNG instead of terminal using alternate color sets
  (XT, ANSI.SYS, XTERM, etc)
	- see https://unix4lyfe.org/cp437/ for RAW font files

